bution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Coudray was born in 1270, in Ormskirk, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert de Coudray, was 31 and his mother, Anota de Whittingham, was 35. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Joan DeMeols. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"1270–":"1270–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1275–Female":"1275–Surnud","1295–1350":"1295–1350","1325–1362":"1325–1362","1240–Male":"1240–Surnud","1235–Female":"1235–Surnud","1325":"1325","1235":"1235","1275":"1275","1362":"1362","1240":"1240","1350":"1350","1295":"1295","1270":"1270","about 1295":"umbes 1295","Ormskirk, Lancashire, England":"Ormskirk, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1270–":"1270–Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1275–Female":"1275–Kuollut","1295–1350":"1295–1350","1325–1362":"1325–1362","1240–Male":"1240–Kuollut","1235–Female":"1235–Kuollut","1325":"1325","1235":"1235","1275":"1275","1362":"1362","1240":"1240","1350":"1350","1295":"1295","1270":"1270","about 1295":"noin 1295","Ormskirk, Lancashire, England":"Ormskirk, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1270–":"1270–Décédé","1270–Male":"1270–Décédé","1275–Female":"1275–Décédée","1295–1350":"1295–1350","1325–1362":"1325–1362","1240–Male":"1240–Décédé","1235–Female"